</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,381,1511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1153,1178]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[765,882,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicName box="[765,878,1153,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electrinus">electrinus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
amber-yellow, in reference to the yellow patches on the wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,381,1511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1220,1245]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[358,590,1220,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[358,590,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Drephalys electrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[598,661,1220,1245]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[598,661,1220,1245]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known from southwestern Amazonia, with records in the Brazilian states of 
<collectingRegion box="[249,303,1254,1278]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Acre</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[357,479,1254,1278]" country="Peru" name="Amazonas" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[539,635,1254,1278]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">paratype</typeStatus>
was collected in the northern region of the Parque Nacional da Serra do Divisor, Mâncio 
<collectingRegion box="[340,402,1286,1311]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Lima</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[413,470,1287,1311]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Acre</collectingRegion>
, close to the border between 
<collectingCountry box="[797,865,1286,1311]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[920,975,1288,1311]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="576" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,381,1511]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1320,1345]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Comments.</emphasis>
This new species is an additional yellow-checkered species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1893" box="[1220,1336,1320,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1336,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Drephalys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Among these, 
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[223,368,1353,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[223,368,1353,1378]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. electrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[376,441,1353,1378]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[376,441,1353,1378]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only one that has a valva without the lateral projection of the costa. The long and slender aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[387,534,1387,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="electrinus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[387,534,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. electrinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[544,610,1387,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,610,1387,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande, 2018" authorityName="Siewert &amp; Madruga &amp; Dolibaina &amp; Mielke &amp; Casagrande" authorityYear="2018" box="[852,989,1387,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Drephalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dracarys" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[852,989,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">D. dracarys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[998,1065,1387,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[998,1065,1387,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differing from the latter by the twisted and serrated tip. These two species are sympatric in the Parque Nacional da Serra do Divisor, 
<collectingRegion box="[1325,1382,1421,1445]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">Acre</collectingRegion>
, and although captured in different events, they were attracted by the Ahrenholz technique (
<bibRefCitation box="[1129,1334,1453,1478]" pageId="3" pageNumber="576" refId="ref4528" refString="Lamas, G., Mielke, O. H. H. &amp; Robbins, R. K. (1993) The Ahrenholz technique for attracting tropical skippers (Hesperiidae). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 47 (1), 80 - 82. Mielke, O. H. H. (1968) Duas especies novas de Drephalys, provenientes de Santa Catarina (Lepidoptera, Hesperiiade). Atas da Sociedade de Biologia do Rio de Janeiro, 12 (3), 129 - 133." type="journal article">
Lamas 
<emphasis box="[1213,1263,1453,1478]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">et al</emphasis>
. 1993
</bibRefCitation>
) without the presence of ants (Austin 
<emphasis box="[470,520,1486,1511]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="576">et al</emphasis>
. 1993).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
